# Frontend Patterns

## React

- Functional components only. Named exports: `export function TaskForm(...)`.
- Props: Explicit interfaces (`TaskFormProps`, `TaskListProps`). Use `type` for shared types.
- State: `useState`, `useCallback` for stable handlers. `useRef` for intervals/DOM refs.
- Colocate component logic. Extract reusable hooks only when logic is shared.
- Prefer existing components; prioritize style and reusability when adding features.

## Styling (index.css)

- BEM-like class names: `.task-form`, `.task-form-container`, `.task-item`, `.task-header`.
- CSS variables in `:root` for theme. Dark-first palette (`#0f172a`, `#1e293b`).
- Section comments: `/* ── Task form ────────────────────────────────── */`
- Responsive: `@media (max-width: 520px)` for mobile. `prefers-reduced-motion` for accessibility.
- Inline styles only for dynamic values (e.g. `width: ${progress}%`, `color: STATUS_COLORS[status]`).

## API

- Fetch `/api/tasks` (proxied to Producer). Poll every 3s for live status.
- FormData for CSV upload: `POST /api/tasks` with `file` and optional `name`.
- Handle errors: `res.ok` check, `body?.error` from JSON. Surface in UI.
